parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Trailing Arm Failure Due to Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear trailing arm can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries. The corrosion of the trailing arm can lead to sudden failure, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle.
symptoms: The rear wheel leans inward or outward
the vehicle sways or loses control
a loud noise or clunking sound is heard from the rear of the vehicle
the vehicle is difficult to steer or handle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Coil Spring Failure Due to Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front coil spring can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries. The corrosion of the coil spring can lead to sudden failure, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle leans to one side
the front tire rubs against the wheel well
a loud noise or clunking sound is heard from the front of the vehicle
the vehicle is difficult to steer or handle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lower Control Arm Failure Due to Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower control arm can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries. The corrosion of the control arm can lead to sudden failure, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle.
symptoms: The wheel detaches from the rotor
a loud noise or clunking sound is heard from the front or rear of the vehicle
the vehicle is difficult to steer or handle.
